I"š<p>The DOM levels are referencing the position of the elements in the heirarchy of the document. As displayed below, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;div&gt;</code> is the parent element and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;h1&gt;</code> is the child element. <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;div&gt;</code> would be on level 1 of the DOM and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">&lt;h1&gt;</code> would be on level 2 of the DOM.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">div</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>
<span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="n">h1</span><span class="o">&gt;</span><span class="no">Hello</span><span class="o">&lt;</span><span class="sr">/h1&gt;
&lt;/</span><span class="n">div</span><span class="o">&gt;</span>  </code></pre></figure>
